value.0: It is a simple chair but the grace of its lines speaks to the quality of its craftmanship.

The following is an excerpt taken from the most recently inscribed page of the book:

"Oh the humanity!!  Oh the humanity!!  Loneliness sets in again...seems I can make all of the creations that I dream, yet to have them speak?  No!! I cannot do it!  Surrounded by cantankerous cold hearted clods who dribble oil from their useless mouths.  What I need are tongues from still living humanoids to complete these miserable masses of metal...."

The following is an excerpt taken from the most recently inscribed page of the book:

"What a failure I am!!  Oh Dread!!  I cannot believe how bad that last one turned out.  I had to banish that frightful ferrous thing to the Failed Experiments chamber.  What a foul place that has turned out to be!!  Even I would never dare to step foot entirely into the place, I almost DIED getting the last one in there...."

"Reminder to self....NEVER, EVER go in there....EVER!!"
